.DT
rows
Discworld player help
rows

.SH Name
.SI 5
rows - Set the number of rows on your screen.
.EI

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
options terminal rows=[number]
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5
Rows is used to set the number of rows on your display that you are using
to play the mud.  The default is 24 and setting it to anything that is not a
valid value, will set it to 24.  Rows on its own shows the current value.
.EP

.SH Examples
.SI 5
> options terminal rows
> options terminal rows=55
> options terminal rows=24
.EI

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
cols, term, colour, options
.EP
